547
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:43,060
Why was it so hard to say that?

548
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:45,170
Your whole life...

549
00:42:45,170 --> 00:42:46,800
Why...

550
00:42:47,870 --> 00:42:50,070
Why?

551
00:42:50,070 --> 00:42:55,030
I wasn't trying to play ignorant forever.

552
00:42:55,660 --> 00:42:59,670
I was going to tell you that day.

553
00:43:01,270 --> 00:43:06,930
 I wanted to tell you before you gave birth to Ah Rin.

554
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:16,210
Jae Won,

555
00:43:16,210 --> 00:43:20,430
please remember this one thing.

556
00:43:21,490 --> 00:43:23,850
It's not because...

557
00:43:24,820 --> 00:43:28,530
I didn't...

558
00:43:28,530 --> 00:43:30,480
love you.

559
00:43:31,610 --> 00:43:33,350
I just...

560
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:38,090
didn't realize that because I was immature then.

561
00:43:40,930 --> 00:43:42,640
Jae Won,

562
00:43:44,650 --> 00:43:46,790
I'm so sorry.

563
00:43:48,480 --> 00:43:50,370
I'm sorry.

564
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:56,230
I'm sorry.

565
00:44:16,840 --> 00:44:18,660
Now...

566
00:44:19,670 --> 00:44:23,250
forget all the bad memories.

567
00:44:23,250 --> 00:44:28,850
Only remember the happy and good memories.

568
00:44:30,160 --> 00:44:32,420
You must...

569
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:37,010
do that for yourself.

570
00:44:39,580 --> 00:44:41,460
I will.

571
00:44:54,390 --> 00:44:57,390
 I know she wasn't real.

572
00:44:57,390 --> 00:45:00,730
She was just an illusion I created.

573
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:04,130
But I had to do that—

574
00:45:04,130 --> 00:45:06,250
I'm glad you did.

575
00:45:06,250 --> 00:45:09,840
You took a step forward, Ms. Seo.

576
00:45:11,540 --> 00:45:13,420
Is that so?

577
00:45:23,810 --> 00:45:27,420
Mom, there's a dead bird here!

578
00:45:27,420 --> 00:45:29,500
Ah Rin.

579
00:45:35,210 --> 00:45:37,530
You're right.

580
00:45:37,530 --> 00:45:40,510
I wonder what happened.

581
00:45:40,510 --> 00:45:42,970
I feel bad for him.

582
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:47,200
Should we bury him?

583
00:45:47,200 --> 00:45:49,640
- Yes.
 - Okay.

584
00:45:54,550 --> 00:45:57,000
Goodbye, birdie.

585
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:00,450
Rest easy in heaven.

586
00:46:00,450 --> 00:46:02,770
Goodbye.

587
00:46:04,390 --> 00:46:06,330
Well done.

588
00:46:21,710 --> 00:46:24,700
Mom, where are we?

589
00:46:28,530 --> 00:46:30,400
This is...

590
00:46:33,080 --> 00:46:35,140
where Dad is.

591
00:46:35,140 --> 00:46:39,070
Dad? Is he here?

592
00:46:39,070 --> 00:46:41,340
- Yes.
 - Where?

593
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:43,060
Where is he?

594
00:46:43,060 --> 00:46:44,230
Dad!

595
00:46:44,230 --> 00:46:45,790
Ah Rin...

596
00:46:48,260 --> 00:46:51,050
He is here, but...

597
00:46:52,050 --> 00:46:54,800
you won't be able to meet him.

598
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,440
Why?

599
00:46:57,890 --> 00:47:01,270
Just like the little bird,

600
00:47:01,270 --> 00:47:04,000
he went to heaven.

601
00:47:05,300 --> 00:47:10,980
Just like the stone grave we made for the little birdie,

602
00:47:10,980 --> 00:47:14,550
this place protects Dad and keeps him warm.

603
00:47:14,550 --> 00:47:18,140
Is he dead?

604
00:47:19,070 --> 00:47:23,300
- Yes.
 - That's why you couldn't tell me, right?

605
00:47:24,190 --> 00:47:25,580
Yes.

606
00:47:27,850 --> 00:47:30,990
I'm sorry I couldn't tell you...

607
00:47:35,960 --> 00:47:39,900
Dad went to heaven early, Ah Rin.

608
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:43,960
Dad.

609
00:47:57,430 --> 00:48:00,970
I miss him a lot, too.

610
00:48:03,170 --> 00:48:05,960
Dad!

611
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:14,700
 Heo Sun Yeong

612
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:20,430
Dad, I missed you.

613
00:48:21,640 --> 00:48:28,460
My English improved a lot while I was in the US.

614
00:48:28,460 --> 00:48:34,940
I'll get a perfect score every day and visit you to brag about it.

615
00:48:34,940 --> 00:48:41,570
So, don't forget to watch me.

616
00:48:41,570 --> 00:48:43,910
Okay?

617
00:48:43,910 --> 00:48:47,710
Dad, I love you.

618
00:49:13,470 --> 00:49:18,150
How's the new collaboration project you mentioned going?

619
00:49:18,150 --> 00:49:20,560
I sent the proposal to the designer.

620
00:49:20,560 --> 00:49:23,860
The design team will have a meeting with her next week.

621
00:49:23,860 --> 00:49:26,950
Shouldn't she have a meeting with me first?

622
00:49:26,950 --> 00:49:31,260
This is our first collaboration with a freelance designer.

623
00:49:31,260 --> 00:49:35,750
I'll decide whether we'll go forward with the project after I meet her.

624
00:49:35,750 --> 00:49:40,320
Contact her and say I want to have a meeting today.

625
00:49:41,550 --> 00:49:44,690
I'll ask if she is available.

626
00:49:54,970 --> 00:49:58,360
How could a designer make the CEO wait?

627
00:49:58,360 --> 00:50:00,750
Does this make any sense?

628
00:50:00,750 --> 00:50:02,850
It sort of does.

629
00:50:04,820 --> 00:50:07,230
Should I call her?

630
00:50:07,230 --> 00:50:09,310
Let's wait five more minutes.

631
00:50:14,830 --> 00:50:17,280
Sorry, I'm late.

632
00:50:17,280 --> 00:50:19,190
You're three minutes late, Ms. Seo.

633
00:50:19,190 --> 00:50:23,490
I'm sorry. I was contacted out of the blue.

634
00:50:23,490 --> 00:50:25,180
Have a seat.

635
00:50:28,140 --> 00:50:29,630
You brought the portfolio, right?

636
00:50:29,630 --> 00:50:31,480
Yes, here it is.

637
00:50:36,980 --> 00:50:39,980
Yes, you're as good as I heard.

638
00:50:39,980 --> 00:50:41,810
Thank you.

639
00:50:43,150 --> 00:50:46,070
You'll be working as the team leader

640
00:50:46,070 --> 00:50:49,400
of the new line for this project.

641
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:53,440
And you'll be working with us here at Derêve, too.

642
00:50:54,950 --> 00:50:57,110
Will you be okay with that?

643
00:51:03,370 --> 00:51:05,600
Just come back.

644
00:51:09,530 --> 00:51:13,510
I'm in your care now, Team Leader Seo Jae Won.

645
00:51:13,510 --> 00:51:17,290
I hope we get along, CEO Yun Te Oh.

646
00:51:22,640 --> 00:51:24,920
How does it feel

647
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:28,300
to become independent as a freelance designer?

648
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:30,430
It feels great.

649
00:51:32,370 --> 00:51:34,260
I see.

650
00:51:34,260 --> 00:51:37,900
You forced me to become the CEO.

651
00:51:37,900 --> 00:51:41,310
And I've been working overtime every day,

652
00:51:41,310 --> 00:51:43,320
but you're happy.

653
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:47,070
It's nighttime, but the weather is nice.

654
00:51:50,670 --> 00:51:52,350
You know what?

655
00:51:53,100 --> 00:51:57,300
You seem very relaxed these days.

656
00:51:58,450 --> 00:52:01,430
Yes, I'm relaxed.

657
00:52:02,330 --> 00:52:05,600
Sketching and making furniture all day

658
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:09,310
seems to make my worries disappear.

659
00:52:11,100 --> 00:52:15,880
I started this because I enjoyed designing so much.

660
00:52:15,880 --> 00:52:19,270
I wonder why I'd been forgetting this feeling.

661
00:52:19,270 --> 00:52:21,010
That's a relief.

662
00:52:21,690 --> 00:52:24,320
Do whatever you want to do and

663
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:28,110
enjoy the moment as much as possible.

664
00:52:30,660 --> 00:52:33,120
Thank you, Te Oh.

665
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:36,080
It must've been a difficult decision,

666
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:39,000
but you took over Derêve for me.

667
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:41,240
Thank you so much.

668
00:52:49,340 --> 00:52:51,200
Here we go again.

669
00:52:51,200 --> 00:52:54,400
You keep thanking me because you're worried I might quit.

670
00:52:54,400 --> 00:52:56,240
You got me.

671
00:53:14,100 --> 00:53:16,290
If you're so thankful,

672
00:53:20,500 --> 00:53:23,820
do you want to come to the meeting with the finance team later?

673
00:53:24,360 --> 00:53:26,400
Look, I finished it.

674
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:28,700
You should manage it yourself, CEO.

675
00:53:30,000 --> 00:53:32,420
How can you do this to me?

676
00:53:32,420 --> 00:53:33,690
Gosh.

677
00:53:33,690 --> 00:53:37,330
How about the sales team or the HR meeting?

678
00:53:46,920 --> 00:53:51,530
Why don't you pick something nicer since you're going to Santiago?

679
00:53:51,530 --> 00:53:52,750
What are you doing here?

680
00:53:52,750 --> 00:53:56,800
I'm watching you so you don't do anything stupid again.

681
00:53:58,760 --> 00:54:00,580
These look good.

682
00:54:01,780 --> 00:54:04,520
Should I get these?

683
00:54:06,580 --> 00:54:09,340
- Are you coming, too?
 - Give me a freaking break.

684
00:54:10,380 --> 00:54:12,650
This is to celebrate you leaving jail.

685
00:54:13,260 --> 00:54:15,510
What size do you wear?

686
00:54:19,780 --> 00:54:22,800
What are you doing here? Are you coming, too?

687
00:54:22,800 --> 00:54:26,990
I brought a scoop that you'd be very interested in, Detective Nam.

688
00:54:26,990 --> 00:54:28,850
Would you like to hear it?

689
00:54:30,110 --> 00:54:32,090
I don't want it.

690
00:54:33,690 --> 00:54:37,610
This is a huge deal, Detective Nam!

691
00:54:37,610 --> 00:54:39,910
Those bastards.

